\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/btoa\"><code>btoa()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/clearInterval\"><code>clearInterval()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/clearTimeout\"><code>clearTimeout()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/createImageBitmap\"><code>createImageBitmap()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/fetch\"><code>fetch()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/queueMicrotask\"><code>queueMicrotask()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/reportError\"><code>reportError()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/setInterval\"><code>setInterval()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/setTimeout\"><code>setTimeout()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/structuredClone\"><code>structuredClone()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BeforeInstallPromptEvent\"><code>BeforeInstallPromptEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/ClipboardEvent\"><code>ClipboardEvent</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CompositionEvent\"><code>CompositionEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/ErrorEvent\"><code>ErrorEvent</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FocusEvent\"><code>FocusEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/FontFaceSetLoadEvent\"><code>FontFaceSetLoadEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Force_Touch_events\"><code>Force_Touch_events</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HashChangeEvent\"><code>HashChangeEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/KeyboardEvent\"><code>KeyboardEvent</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaRecorderErrorEvent\"><code>MediaRecorderErrorEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStreamTrackEvent\"><code>MediaStreamTrackEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MouseScrollEvent\"><code>MouseScrollEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-nonstandard\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MSManipulationEvent\"><code>MSManipulationEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PictureInPictureEvent\"><code>PictureInPictureEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TaskPriorityChangeEvent\"><code>TaskPriorityChangeEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Touch_events\"><code>Touch_events</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/UIEvent\"><code>UIEvent</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRReferenceSpaceEvent\"><code>XRReferenceSpaceEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSessionEvent\"><code>XRSessionEvent</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p><span>The <strong><code>Body</code></strong> <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Mixin\">mixin <small>(en-US)</small></a> of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Fetch_API\">Fetch API</a> represents the body of the response/request, allowing you to declare what its content type is and how it should be handled.</span></p>\n\n<p><code>Body</code> is implemented by both <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Request\"><code>Request</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> and <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Response\"><code>Response</code></a>. This provides these objects with an associated <dfn>body</dfn> (a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Streams_API\">stream</a>), a <dfn>used flag</dfn> (initially unset), and a <dfn>MIME type</dfn> (initially the empty byte sequence).</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"body.body_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Response/body\"><code>Body.body</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n <dd>A simple getter used to expose a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ReadableStream\"><code>ReadableStream</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> of the body contents.</dd>\n <dt id=\"body.bodyused_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Response/bodyUsed\"><code>Body.bodyUsed</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n <dd>A <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Boolean\"><code>Boolean</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> that indicates whether the body has been read.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"body.arraybuffer_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Response/arrayBuffer\"><code>Body.arrayBuffer()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Takes a <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Response\"><code>Response</code></a> stream and reads it to completion. It returns a promise that resolves with an&nbsp;<a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\"><code>ArrayBuffer</code></a>.</dd>\n <dt id=\"body.blob_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Response/blob\"><code>Body.blob()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Takes a <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Response\"><code>Response</code></a> stream and reads it to completion. It returns a promise that resolves with a <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a>.</dd>\n <dt id=\"body.formdata_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Response/formData\"><code>Body.formData()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Takes a <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Response\"><code>Response</code></a> stream and reads it to completion. It returns a promise that resolves with a <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/FormData\"><code>FormData</code></a> object.</dd>\n <dt id=\"body.json\"><a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/orphaned/Web/API/Body/json\"><code>Body.json()</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Takes a <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Response\"><code>Response</code></a> stream and reads it to completion. It returns a promise that resolves with the result of parsing the body text as <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON\"><code>JSON</code></a>.</dd>\n <dt id=\"body.text_en-us\"><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Response/text\"><code>Body.text()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></dt>\n <dd>Takes a <a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Response\"><code>Response</code></a> stream and reads it to completion. It returns a promise that resolves with a <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\"><code>USVString</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> (text). The response is <em>always</em> decoded using UTF-8.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The example below uses a simple fetch call to grab an image and display it in an <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/img\"><code>&lt;img&gt;</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> tag. You'll notice that since we are requesting an image, we need to run <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Response/blob\"><code>Body.blob()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> (<a href=\"/zh-TW/docs/Web/API/Response\"><code>Response</code></a> implements body) to give the response its correct MIME type.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"html_content","title":"HTML Content","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>img</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>my-image<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>https://wikipedia.org/static/images/project-logos/frwiki-1.5x.png<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"js_content","title":"JS Content","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> myImage <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">querySelector</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'.my-image'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">fetch</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/77/Delete_key1.jpg'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">res</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> res<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">blob</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">res</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> objectURL <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token constant\">URL</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">createObjectURL</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>res<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\t\tmyImage<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>src <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> objectURL<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n\n<p><iframe class=\"sample-code-frame\" title=\"Examples sample\" id=\"frame_examples\" width=\"100%\" height=\"250px\" src=\"https://yari-demos.prod.mdn.mozit.cloud/zh-TW/docs/orphaned/Web/API/Body/_sample_.examples.html\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specifications","title":"Specifications","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Specification</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Comment</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#body-mixin\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Fetch<br><small lang=\"zh-TW\">The definition of 'Body' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Living Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"data":null,"query":"api.Body","browsers":null}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Service_Worker_API\">ServiceWorker API</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/CORS\">HTTP access control (CORS)</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP\">HTTP</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The Body mixin (en-US) of the Fetch API represents the body of the response/request, allowing you to declare what its content type is and how it should be handled.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","source":{"folder":"zh-tw/orphaned/web/api/body","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/zh-tw/orphaned/web/api/body/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"pageTitle":"Body | MDN","noIndexing":true}}